<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-712-954  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 712 954.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Personal Computing  Oct 1989 v13 n10 p31(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Technology that gets you where you live. (working-at-homemovement) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hedberg, Augustin.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Why have so many workers begun working at home? Students ofeconomics claim it is due to the business cycle.andP;  A recession maybe close, and workers are getting laid off in large numbers.andO;Sociologists' statistics show these workers to be content at home,possessing high work-style satisfaction.andP;  The average worker is 39years old and is part of a dual-career household.andP;  Their totalhousehold income averages $42,000, or 20 percent above thenational average.andP;  The working-at-home movement will probably notdisappear with economic or demographic changes.andP;  The advantages ofworking in a comfortable environment and still keepingprofessional contacts are too significant to reject.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Work at HomeWork EnvironmentErgonomicsTrendsMicrocomputers.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>